here are the latest statistics on acquired immune 
deficiency syndrome in the united states as reported this week by 
the national centers for disease control 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
total cases reported since june 1981 84985 
cases year to date 2228 
total deaths 48582 or 57 percent of all cases 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
homosexual or bisexual males 51581 or 61 percent 
intravenous drug abusers 16672 or 20 percent 
homosexual male and drug abusers 6013 or 7 percent 
heterosexual cases 3685 or 4 percent 
transfusion or blood cases 2256 or 3 percent 
hemophilia patients 882 or 1 percent 
children of parents with aids or at risk 1080 or 1 percent 
undetermined transmission cause 2816 or 3 percent 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
childhood cases under age 13 1393 or 2 percent 
cases among whites 48808 or 57 percent 
cases among blacks 22579 or 27 percent 
cases among hispanics 12817 or 15 percent 
cases among asians or pacific islanders 502 or 1 percent 
cases among american indians or alaskan natives 90 or 0 percent 
 
note these statistics are through jan 30 and have been rounded 
to the nearest whole percent cumulative totals are for aids cases 
reported since june 1981 and include 75 cases subsequently found to 
have occurred prior to that date 
