<TEXT>
black muslim minister louis farrakhan 
appeared thursday at the racially troubled university of 
massachusetts and angrily told jewish protesters they had no right 
to call him a hatemonger 
farrakhan told an audience of 2000 that he did not come to the 
college to pit blacks against jews but he said blacks learned how 
to hate from the hatred directed at them 
to those jewish students who see me as a hitler as a hater i 
wish you life i wish you life i dont wish to see any human 
forfeit his life said the leader of the chicagobased nation of 
islam 
but farrakhan added your people taught us to hate ourselves 
for years and you have a hell of a nerve to see me today and call 
me a hatemonger 
farrakhan said whites should leave blacks to solve their problems 
themselves 
if the jewish students come together to work out some family 
matter we shouldnt call that racism he said no one outside 
the family should dare to interfere with our family problems 
he said more separation between the races is needed to combat 
black feelings of inferiority 
we dont need a bedroom relationship with white people we want 
a boardroom relationship perhaps some other time we might want to 
entertain some social contacts 
farrakhan added when we awaken we will march against every 
vestige of oppression and if you challenge us then we are going to 
clash with you until death separates us from life or you from life 
but why should that be 
more than 500 students held a quiet candlelight march prior to 
farrakhans visit while members of a militant jewish group led 
students in a loud demonstration outside the hall in which the black 
leader spoke 
farrakhan is a nazi without a swastika declared mordechai 
levi the new yorkbased head of the jewish defense organization 
he should be in libya not in this campus 
the visit by farrakhan and the 38 guards he calls the fruit of 
islam nearly coincided with the first anniversary of a campus 
building takeover by 100 minority students to protest racial 
violence at this 30000student school in western massachusetts 
farrakhan was promised 11000 by a black fraternity and a campus 
speaker program to talk at the universitys fine arts center 
tickets sold out within a day 
farrakhan came to national attention in 1984 for calling judaism 
a gutter religion and making other antisemitic remarks that his 
supporters say have been taken out of context in his campaign to 
foster black pride 
the amherst campus has been the scene of racial strife since a 
fight broke out among black and white students after the boston red 
sox loss to the new york mets in the final game of the 1986 world 
series 
on feb 11 1988 minority students began a weeklong occupation 
of a university building to protest another racial scuffle the 
takeover which was the first of several around the northeast ended 
with the chancellors agreement to boost programs for minority 
students 
