<TEXT>
the san jose police officers association 
has filed a lawsuit demanding that 500 officers be added to the 
police force in response to the recent deaths of two patrolmen in a 
shootout with a transient 
the association which represents 970 of san joses 1014member 
police force said the current level of 136 officers per 1000 
residents in san jose is inadequate to assure reasonable police and 
public safety and is far below the national average of 258 officers 
per 1000 
mayor tom mcenery called the associations demand for a 50 
percent increase spelled out in a lawsuit filed thursday 
fiscally impossible and unrealistic 
in making the demand which is estimated to cost 25 million 
annually the association is relying on a state labor code provision 
requiring employers to adopt reasonable safety standards for 
workers it may be the first such use of the provision 
with a total of 1500 officers the force would have about two 
officers per 1000 population more than 742000 people live in san 
jose 
the city council on thursday approved mcenerys request for 15 
more officers this spring as part of the midyear budget review the 
mayor said he plans to ask the council for an addition 40 to 50 
officers 
carm grande president of the association conceded the hiring of 
500 officers at one time is an impossible project and said the 
association was willing to negotiate a time period when that many 
officers could be added 
the lawsuit filed in superior court which names as defendants 
the city mcenery the city manager and the city council added fuel 
to a heated debate over police staffing and procedures since the 
jan 20 gun battle in which officers gene simpson and gordon silva 
were killed along with gunman dale randell connors simpson was shot 
with his own gun when connors a transient grabbed the weapon 
during a struggle 
in its suit the association also asked for two officers per 
patrol car but grande said he would drop that demand if the city 
agreed to hire 500 more officers 
mcenery dismissed the need for so many more police arguing that 
despite the recent shootings san jose is the safest big city in 
america 
an fbi report last july showed that san jose has only six violent 
crimes per 1000 population far below detroits 254 per thousand 
portlands 224 new yorks 204 chicagos 196 and los angeles 
191 
san jose also had the lowest homicide rate of californias 10 
largest cities in 1987 when it had 26 killings the city had 30 
killings in 1988 but already has 13 so far this year grande said 
grande said the officers chose to fight the city in court after 
getting nowhere in negotiations 
the mayor has indicated over the past years that he supports 
the police department but we see nothing forthcoming from his 
office grande said 
