the lifesize sculptures were made by port arthur artist doug 
clark for the citys historical society which began its sculpture 
collection last year with clarks portait of rock queen janis 
joplin a port arthur native who died in 1970 
clark said he worked from videotapes of richardson and holly and 
from photos of valens his pose of the three with the boppers 
arms around valens and holly is intended to show the trio as if 
they were standing for a picture just before boarding the fateful 
flight to fargo 
i dont know that there really is such a picture clark said 
but i could just imagine someone getting one last shot before they 
got on the airplane 
a second sculpture of richardson alone shows the wideeyed 
grinning singer with a guitar at his waist and his arms wide open 
proceeds from todays event will go toward the purchase of a 
50000 building for a port arthur museum that would include rock 
n roll memorabilia 
