replace all three of them on the launch pad in conjunction with 
other work they also postponed the launch from late february to 
midmarch 
the problem stems from an atlantis flight in december a 
postflight inspection of the shuttles engines disclosed two tiny 
cracks in a bearing housing in one of three highspeed turbopumps 
that convert liquid oxygen to a gas 
engineers believe the cracks were caused by stress corrosion 
resulting from moisture trapped inside the housing during the 
manufacturing process because two of discoverys turbopumps 
underwent the same processing nasa decided to replace all three 
pumps with new carefullyinspected units 
the pumps are a critical component because the shuttle could 
explode if one failed during liftoff 
in the past turbopumps have been replaced while a shuttle was 
horizontal in a checkout building but discovery is now in a 
vertical position and without previous experience there is an 
uncertainty about how long the replacement will take the new pumps 
are scheduled to arrive here the week of feb 12 
discovery will be commanded by astronaut michael coats with him 
