<TEXT>
india used heavy water purchased from the 
savannah river plant in its nuclear weapons program despite 
assurances it wouldnt do so a nuclear expert said 
india exploded a nuclear weapon in 1974 soon after the united 
states and canada which had supplied both nuclear technology and 
heavy water to india cut off shipments india then turned to the 
soviet union for its heavy water 
the savannah river plant in nearby aiken sc at one time sold 
heavy water to 21 countries including eight with nuclear weapons 
programs 
those countries were argentina brazil england france india 
israel pakistan and south africa according to records cited by the 
augusta chronicle and the augusta herald 
england france and india have exploded nuclear weapons israel 
south africa and pakistan either have or are capable of producing 
such weapons and argentina and brazil are close said leonard 
