international peace 
india received 36 tons of heavy water in seven sales made in 
1954 1959 and 1960 it returned 15 tons of the water records show 
the heavy water was sold to a facility that was not under 
inspection but india promised it was not being used to produce 
nuclear weapons spector said it looked like a clear 
violation 
spector said most of the heavy water used by india in producing 
its bomb was from other countries but american heavy water had 
been involved 
heavy water is used as a moderator or primary coolant in some 
nuclear reactors including those at srp 
the atomic energy act and its amendments allowed the department 
