<TEXT>
satellite television beams its way to britain on 
sunday with much fanfare but few viewers 
when media magnate rupert murdoch launches his fourchannel sky 
television network the number of channels available to most britons 
will instantly double 
but the equipment needed to receive the satellite signals in 
british homes is in short supply and will be for several more weeks 
if not months 
