giving just a fraction of the 56 million britons a chance to watch 
the 6 pm premiere 
watching television is britains most popular leisure activity 
even with only four regular channels two commercial and two run by 
the statefunded british broadcasting corp 
direct satellitetohome television has been hailed as a 
revolution in british broadcasting and the beginning of a new 
skirmish between britains two biggest newspaper publishers who 
both are trying to crack the satellite market 
time out the weekly guide to whats happening in london has 
billed it the biggest aerial dogfight since the battle of 
britain and a noholds barred star wars 
critics praising the highquality shows now produced in britain 
already have turned up their noses at murdochs programming which 
will rely heavily on imported american soap operas situation 
comedies and game shows 
michael grade chief executive of the highbrow commercial channel 
4 called it junk fastfood takeaway telly 
sky television will be vying with a consortium involving rival 
publisher robert maxwell and a third international consortium 
british satellite broadcasting bsb 
murdoch has managed to get sky on the air seven months before 
bsbs target date 
hes using the astra satellite owned by a luxembourgbased group 
and put into orbit in december 
bsb was awarded three of the five channels on another satellite 
under international treaty that satellite isnt scheduled to be 
launched until august and programming is not expected until 
september 
maxwells two channels screen sport and lifestyle also will be 
bounced off the astra satellite as soon as contractual snags are 
ironed out said spokesman chris howland maxwells two channels and 
one of murdochs now are available only to british cable subscribers 
cable subscribers have more channels than the regular four but 
very fewer britons have cable it is available in only three of 
londons 32 boroughs plus a handful of other cities the cable 
television association says there are 265645 subscribers 
sky television and bsb will use incompatible technologies so 
those wanting to subscribe to both must buy two receiving dishes and 
descramblers 
sky television says it hopes its head start will persuade 
television fans to buy its technology 
all four sky television channels news movies light 
entertainment and sports will initially be offered free 
this summer just before the bsb launch sky television will add 
the disney channel and an arts channel which along with the movie 
channel will arrive scrambled for a monthly subscription fee 
viewers will then receive a small credit card to plug into a 
receiving box and decode the signal 
eurosport will kick off sunday with davis cup tennis sky channel 
the light entertainment channel now available on cable with a 
