statute that was amended in 1986 to allow whistleblowers to collect 
a percentage of judgments against companies that cheat the 
government 
the justice department said it had elected not to join the 
lawsuit after a review and investigation of the case 
the department added however that it would continue to monitor 
the case brought by a former software manager and a technician 
currently employed at the plant 
the statute allows the government to intervene at a later time 
