gen alfredo stroessners long tenure 
as dictator ended because he tampered too much with the institution 
that propelled him into power 34 years ago the military 
stroessner tried to force his most powerful military leader gen 
andres rodriguez into retirement and his recent shakeups of the 
army caused widespread resentment among his officers 
that combined with stroessners ultimate plans to have his son 
succeed him as president led to the violent coup that ended the 
76yearold generals rule and vaulted rodriguez to power on friday 
stroessner tried to take away some of the regiments controlled 
by rodriguez and thus reduce his power a technique he stroessner 
has used for years but this time he committed a very big 
indiscretion edgar insfran an interior minister for 10 years 
during the 1950s and 1960s said in an interview 
