<TEXT>
directoractor john cassavetes known for his 
freewheeling improvisational style in such movies as faces and 
a woman under the influence died friday he was 59 
gena rowlands his wife of three decades and the star of most of 
his films was at his side when he died at cedarssinai medical 
center said his publicist esme chandlee 
he died of complications resulting from cirrhosis of the liver 
ms chandlee said 
cassavetes was one of only four entertainers ever to be nominated 
for an academy award in three different categories ms chandlee 
said he was nominated as best writer for his original screenplay of 
faces in 1968 as best supporting actor in the dirty dozen 
in 1967 and as best director for his original film a woman under 
the influence in 1974 
among cassavetes bestknown acting roles was as the husband of a 
woman who conceives a baby by the devil in rosemarys baby a 
1968 film that also starred mia farrow 
he also starred with miss rowlands susan sarandon and molly 
ringwald in tempest director paul mazurskys film adaptation of 
shakespeares play among other films 
faces which he also directed was a personal probing study 
of loneliness the film won three oscar nominations and five venice 
film festival awards 
a woman under the influence is the story of the souring of a 
middleclass marriage which starred his wife 
i think they both had a great fondness for a woman under the 
influence ms chandlee said of cassavetes and miss rowlands 
it was certainly his most commercial film 
the movie earned miss rowlands a golden globe as best actress and 
an academy award nomination for best actress 
his first movie as a director was shadows filmed from 
195760 on what amounted to pennies using a handheld 16mm camera 
technically the film was a misfit but as an art form it has been 
referred to by film buffs as a masterpiece the movie is about a 
fairskinned black girl living in new york with her two brothers 
the type of films we do are different cassavetes once said 
in an interview with the associated press commercial movies have 
no feeling no sensitivity most people tell me that people wont 
understand films with feeling but everyone can feel 
i think people are very stiff money makes people stiff and we 
want it and we have to pay the penalty i never agreed with 
stiffness i think people have an understanding of what their life 
is i define success by being a realist and not humiliating people 
im a revolutionary but not in the political sense 
in 1980 he was honored by the museum of modern art with a 
retrospective of his works that same year he was also honored by 
filmex the los angeles film festival he was 50 at the time 
by the age of 50 i would like to know that im not dead that 
theres some continuity to my life he said 
cassavetes a native of new york grew up poor his break in 
acting came when he played a brooding young bullfighter in a 
production of the old omnibus tv series in 1953 that led to 
roles in playhouse 90 studio one kraft theater and 
climax his official debut on the silver screen was as an extra 
in 14 hours in 1951 he starred in taxi in 1953 and was in 
the night holds terror in 1955 
he remained an independent filmmaker who marched to the tune of a 
different drummer if it came to a good film or what makes 
feeling id take feeling he once said 
cassavetes developed close friendships with a few actors 
including peter falk a spokeswoman for falk said he was 
devastated by cassavetes death and production of the reprised 
columbo television series was halted so falk could be at home 
alone 
this has been a terrible jolt for peter said his assistant 
april araynell there was a very strong bond between them a love 
between them peter is just trying to hold up any way he can 
cassavetes and miss rowlands were married in march 1958 and their 
careers were seldom separate after that they had three children 
nicholas alexandra and zoe 
cassavetes had a vast enthusiasm for films especially his own 
a woman under the influence rips your guts out he said 
i have seen it 30 times and i cant look at it any more it is too 
powerful an experience 
private funeral services were scheduled for monday in los angeles 
</TEXT>
