<TEXT>
wealthy sir harry oakes was murdered in 1943 
at his home in the bahamas during an apparent voodoo ritual and 
although the scandal reached the level of the duke and duchess of 
windsor his killer is still unknown 
not that there was a lack of suspects they ranged from his 
soninlaw to the mafia from gamblers angered by his opposition to 
their plans for casinos in the islands to a rabblerousing native 
revolutionary 
the murder of oakes and the cast of suspects detectives and 
royalty might have been put together by agatha christie but the 
story is true and is told in the fourhour twopart miniseries 
passion and paradise which airs sunday and tuesday on abc 
the murder was very big in the headlines said catherine mary 
stewart who plays oakes daughter nancy people were very 
anxious to read anything that would take their minds off world war 
ii 
nancys husband alfred de marigny played by armand assante was 
a major suspect in the murder he was penniless and reputedly had 
been a gigolo 
he was a playboy who had married several wealthy women said 
stewart when he started hanging out with nancy the immediate 
suspicion was that he was after the money her parents were totally 
opposed to the marriage he and the father were alike in some ways 
and even advised each other but my husband felt my father had too 
much control over me 
its a fascinating story and what attracted me to nancy is that 
shes such a complex character she starts out as a teenager 
raised in this protected environment in paradise shes bored and 
when she meets this man of the world he sweeps her off her feet 
apparently it was a very passionate relationship 
despite the title oakes was an american who had made a fortune 
as a gold miner in the klondike he moved to the bahamas to take 
advantage of its lenient tax laws 
the miniseries was filmed in jamaica harvey hart directed from a 
screenplay by andrew laskos 
rod steiger plays oakes mariette hartley is his wife michael 
sarrazin is an island gangster and kevin mccarthy is a real estate 
dealer wayne rogers plays raymond schindler an american detective 
called in to investigate the murder 
schindler was a detective nancy brought in because he had been 
a friend of her fathers said stewart hes not your typical 
private eye he was frumpy rumpled a lot like lt colombo wayne 
rogers played him as rather sarcastic wayne himself is the king of 
bad jokes he was always telling these terrible jokes 
i was with some real pros in a courtroom scene all we had to 
do was sit there and react kevin wayne mariette and i watching 
these people perform i got so distracted i was dead in the water 
kevin would cough and pull at his hankerchief then turn and look 
around mariette was doing all her little things it was magnetic 
stewart said she was pleased that she was openly welcomed by the 
other actors they made me feel a part of the group she said 
so often you work with older stars and they keep to themselves 
she said working opposite assante helped her performance hes 
a very disciplined actor she said he kept me on my toes you 
cant let up when you work with armand 
oakes murder occurred while the duke of windsor was governor of 
the bahamas the scandal including a police conspiracy reached 
into his government but mainly he is pictured as inept when the 
scandal heated up the duke and duchess left the islands to avoid 
the publicity 
the legal investigation was very shoddy said stewart the 
duke hired a couple of detectives from miami who already had very 
bad reputations thats why nancy took it upon herself to hire an 
investigator the murder was made to look like a voodoo ritual 
there were bloody handprints on the walls and chicken feathers 
everywhere the bed had been burned 
the next day the murder scene had been cleaned up all the 
evidence was removed the only fingerprint found was nancys 
husbands but that was suspect there were so many loose ends even 
today 
one theory was that oakes had been killed because he was blocking 
legalized gambling in the bahamas mafia gangsters wanted to expand 
their profitable casinos in havana to the bahamas 
immediately after his death gambling was approved for the bahamas 
and the largest casino of all was built on the site of his mansion 
</TEXT>
