<TEXT>
chrysler corp has announced its second foreign 
joint venture this week an estimated 500 million deal with 
frances renault to build a fourwheel drive sport vehicle 
codenamed jj 
the deal announced thursday by chrysler chairman lee a iacocca 
heralds the first european production for the nations no 2 
automaker in more than a decade 
chrysler also said it posted a 238 percent fourthquarter 
earnings increase although annual profits for 1988 shrank 186 
percent and announced its workers would receive 720 in 
profitsharing this year 
iacocca said joint production of the jj called a minisport 
utility vehicle was scheduled to begin in july 1992 at an 
existing us plant and one in either portugal or spain the 
jeeplike vehicle would cost under 10000 he said 
you look at it and its a wow car iacocca told a new york 
news conference 
chrysler earlier this week announced it would market autos made 
in canada by south koreas hyundai motor corp beginning in 1991 
iacocca said the 5050 venture with frances stateowned 
automaker aims to sell 100000 vehicles in the united states and 
50000 in europe he said the companies contribution to the deal 
would total about 500 million 
chrysler will handle north american sales while renault will be 
responsible for france italy portugal and spain 
iacocca also said hourly and salaried workers would receive 
profitsharing payments averaging about 720 in march the payments 
would be the companys first under a profitsharing agreement signed 
last year with the united auto workers 
general motors corp late last year announced profitsharing of 
about 200 per employee officials at no 2 ford motor co are 
expected to announce profitsharing well over 1000 per worker 
chrysler closed at 2850 down 37 cents a share in new york 
stock exchange composite trading thursday 
iacocca also renewed his argument that the us treasury 
department should impose a 25 percent tariff on all imported trucks 
including minivans and sportutility vehicles some foreign 
automakers slightly modify vehicles to classify them as cars such 
as the popular minivans and thereby have to pay only a 25 percent 
tariff 
iacocca gm chairman roger b smith and ford chairman donald 
peterson have called on the treasury to slap the truck tariff on 
lightutility vehicles 
if it looks like a truck and walks like a truck and acts like a 
truck then its a truck iacocca said 
chrysler reported a profit of 4336 million or 185 a share 
in the three months ended dec 31 that compared with earnings of 
3502 million or 157 a share in fourth quarter 1987 
revenue totaled 969 billion up 136 percent from 853 billion 
in the corresponding 1987 quarter 
for the full year chrysler had a profit of 105 billion or 
466 cents a share down 186 percent from 129 billion or 590 
a share in 1987 annual revenue rose to 355 billion from 293 
billion the previous year 
the 1988 results were reduced by 931 million due to a 150 
million charge for previously announced plant closings in chryslers 
acustar parts subsidiary 
iacocca said annual results also were affected by the companys 
strategy to increase market share by reducing some auto prices and 
offering sales incentives 
chryslers share of the us car and truck market rose to 14 
percent from 123 percent in 1987 chrysler said it sold 221 
million vehicles the first time it sold a million cars and a 
million trucks in the same year compared with 192 million in 1987 
chrysler financial corp the automakers financing arm reported 
a fourth quarter profit of 74 million up from 60 million a year 
earlier for the full year chrysler financial had a profit of 259 
million up from 226 million in 1987 
automakers and analysts have predicted 1988 would be the 
industrys best earnings year ever with the big three posting 
combined profits of 11 billion the previous record was the 
combined 98 billion profit in 1984 
general motors corp and ford motor co are expected to release 
their fourthquarter earnings in midfebruary 
