the spokesman outlined the basic points guiding the president 
insured savings must be protected 
current problems must be solved and losses stopped 
permanent reforms preventing a recurrence must be enacted 
the deposit insurance system should be put on a sound financial 
footing 
cleanup costs must be equitably allocated 
sununus anger over the advertisements underscores the 
administrations concern that the debate in washington over how to 
pay for the sampl crisis has unnerved some thrift depositors 
