witter reynolds inc said the employment data were strong enough to 
force the federal reserve to raise shortterm interest rates to slow 
the economy as a hedge against higher inflation 
even if you exclude construction you see a very buoyant set 
of labor data and it does suggest the economy is taking a strong 
tick in the new year he said against that data i would look 
for some tightening in credit policy 
